  "response": "The most abundant rock on Earth is basalt. Basalt is a type of igneous rock that is formed from the rapid cooling of lava at the Earth's surface. It is predominantly found in the oceanic crust and makes up a significant portion of the Earth's surface. The high abundance of basalt is due to the extensive volcanic activity that occurs at mid-ocean ridges, where new oceanic crust is constantly being produced.",
